  "prompt": "Who is the best trance singer other than Arvin?",
  "response": "When discussing the best trance singers or vocalists, it's important to note that trance music often features collaborations with various talented artists rather than being centered around a single \"best\" singer. However, some vocalists have become iconic in the trance scene for their contributions. Here are a few notable names:\n\n1. **Jes Brieden (Jes)** - Known for her work with BT, Dash Berlin, and as a solo artist, Jes is one of the most recognizable voices in trance music. Hits like \"As the Rush Comes\" and \"Imagination\" have cemented her legacy.\n\n2. **Justine Suissa** - A frequent collaborator with Above & Beyond and OceanLab, Justine's ethereal voice has become synonymous with the emotive side of trance. Songs like \"Satellite\" and \"On a Good Day\" are fan favorites.\n\n3. **Emma Hewitt** - With her powerful and emotional vocals, Emma Hewitt has become a staple in the trance world. Tracks like \"Carry Me Away\" and \"Be Your Sound\" (with Cosmic Gate) are classics.\n\n4. **Sarah McLachlan** - While primarily known as a pop artist, Sarah McLachlan's collaboration with Delerium on \"Silence\" became a massive trance anthem after its remix by Tiesto.\n\n5. **Roxanne Emery** - A rising star in the trance scene, Roxanne has worked with artists like Gareth Emery (her brother) and Aly & Fila. Her vocals on tracks like \"Concrete Angel\" and \"All the Shine\" are highly regarded.\n\nThese artists have all made significant contributions to trance music, and their voices have become integral to the genre's emotional and uplifting sound.",
